Hi !
 hope this is not offtopic for here...
 Kernel 2.2.13 running in 4MB RAM gives me Bus Errors that don't 
 kill the box but make it more or less unusable . The problem 
 is load independant , that is bus-errors will occure after booting
 it without any real load on the system . If I put 8MB-RAM in the box
 ( + 4RAM-DISK ) the problem goes away and even with heavy load no bus 
 errors occure. since this error occures with ALL applications I guess its
 not a problem of the applications or the libs but a memory management 
 problem.
 this is the output of /proc/meminfo wherby 4MB ar a RAM-DISK (in which
 Linux is running , no harddisk on this system -> no swap ) there seems
 to plenty of memory free , and this will not change when bus errors occure.
Memory Usage:
